cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC 

This paper focuses on natural language processing techniques to summarise sets of products, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) in terms of extracting relevant features from the product set. The use of machine learning algorithms to identify common product features and their impact on price suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the evaluation of the usefulness of the summaries for customers suggests a potential application in human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
